LAGOS – A BRT bus was on Wednesday morning gutted by fire on Ifako Bridge inward Ogudu, Lagos.The bus, which was on Ifako Bridge inwards Ogudu, coming from Iyana-Oworo, was burning despite the heavy rain in the morning at Ogudu, as men of the Lagos State Fire Service were seen trying to contain the incident, which occurred around 10:25am. Thousands of motorists coming from the Island heading towards Ketu, Ikorodu, among other areas, were left stranded on the bridge.A commercial bus summersautled, and was suspected to have also been involved in the accident. Details Later…